messages.user_correction: Robert Joseph Dole was an American politician, attorney, and U.S. Army officer who represented Kansas in the United States Senate from 1969 to 1996. He was the Republican Leader of the U.S Senate during the final 11 years of his tenure, including three non-consecutive years as Majority Leader of the U.S. Senate.
